text: Nordstromia paralilacina is a moth in the family Drepanidae. It was described by Min Wang and Katsumi Yazaki in 2004. It is found in Guangdong, China.Wang, Min & Yazaki, Katsumi (2004). "A new species of Nordstromia Bryk (Drepanidae: Drepaninae) from S. China". Tinea. 18 (2): 140-142. ==References== Category:Moths described in 2004 Category:Drepaninae
title: Nordstromia paralilacina
